.realmadrid.com/en/football/squad/mateo-kovacic Profile] at the Real Madrid CF website\n*[https://www.chelseafc.com/en/teams/first-team/mateo-kovacic?pageTab=biography Profile] at the Chelsea C.F. website\n*{{UEFA player}}\n*{{FIFA player}}\n\n{{Chelsea F.C. squad}}\n{{Croatian Football Hope of the Year award}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Croatia squads\n| bg = white\n| fg = #171796\n| bordercolor= red\n| list1 = \n{{Croatia squad 2014 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Croatia squad UEFA Euro 2016}}\n{{Croatia squad 2018 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kovacic, Mateo}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Austrian people of Croatian descent]]\n[[Category:Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Austrian people of Bosnia and Herzegovina descent]]\n[[Category:Croatian people of Bosnia and Herzegovina descent]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Linz]]\n[[Category:Austrian footballers]]\n[[Category:Croatian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:GNK Dinamo Zagreb players]]\n[[Category:Inter Milan players]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid CF players]]\n[[Category:Chelsea F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Croatian First Football League players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Champions League winning players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Europa League winning players]]\n[[Category:Croatia under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Croatia international footballers]]\n[[Category:2014 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2016 players]]\n[[Category:2018 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Croatian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Croatian expatriate sportspeople in Italy]]\n[[Category:Croatian expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n[[Category:Croatian expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107\n| image = ISL-HRV (9) (cropped) Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107.jpg\n| image_size = 200\n| caption = Kova\u010di\u0107 with [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]]\n| fullname = Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifadata.com/document/fwc/2014/pdf/fwc_2014_squadlists.pdf |title=2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil: List of Players: Croatia |publisher=FIFA |page=12 |date=14 July 2014 |accessdate=5 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121051710/http://www.fifadata.com/document/fwc/2014/pdf/fwc_2014_squadlists.pdf |archive-date=21 January 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1994|5|6|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifadata.com/documents/FCWC/2017/pdf/FCWC_2017_Squadlists.pdf |title=FIFA Club World Cup UAE 2017: List of players: Real Madrid CF |publisher=FIFA |page=5 |date=16 December 2017 |accessdate=5 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171223004345/http://www.fifadata.com/documents/FCWC/2017/pdf/FCWC_2017_Squadlists.pdf |archive-date=23 December 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Linz]], Austria\n| height = 1.78 m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/12520/Mateo-Kovacic/overview |title=Mateo Kovacic: Overview |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=8 June 2019}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n| clubnumber = 17\n| youthyears1 = 2000\u20132007\n| youthclubs1 = [[LASK Linz]]\n| youthyears2 = 2007\u20132010\n| youthclubs2 = [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb Academy|Dinamo Zagreb]]\n| years1 = 2010\u20132013\n| clubs1 = [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]\n| caps1 = 43\n| goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2013\u20132015\n| clubs2 = [[Inter Milan]]\n| caps2 = 80\n| goals2 = 5\n| years3 = 2015\u20132019\n| clubs3 = [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]\n| caps3 = 73\n| goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 32\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2019\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n| caps5 = 25\n| goals5 = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2008\n| nationalteam1 = Croatia U14\n| nationalcaps1 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2008\n| nationalteam2 = Croatia U15\n| nationalcaps2 = 2\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2009\u20132011\n| nationalteam3 = [[Croatia national under-17 football team|Croatia U17]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 15\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2011\u20132012\n| nationalteam4 = [[Croatia national under-19 football team|Croatia U19]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 6\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| nationalyears5 = 2011\u20132014\n| nationalteam5 = [[Croatia national under-21 football team|Croatia U21]]\n| nationalcaps5 = 7\n| nationalgoals5 = 0\n| nationalyears6 = 2013\u2013\n| nationalteam6 = [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]]\n| nationalcaps6 = 56\n| nationalgoals6 = 1\n| club-update = 18:37, 29 February 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 22:33, 19 November 2019 (UTC)\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{Medal|Country|{{fb|CRO}}}}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[FIFA World Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 Russia]]|}}\n}}\n'''Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107''' ({{IPA-sh|mat\u011bo k\u01d2\u028bat\u0283it\u0255|hr}};<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=e1tnXBk%3D&keyword=Sv.|title=M\u00e0tej|quote=Mat\u00e8o|website=Hrvatski jezi\u010dni portal|accessdate=17 March 2018|language=sh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=ellgUBQ%3D|title=k\u00f2vati|quote=K\u00f2va\u010di\u010d|website=Hrvatski jezi\u010dni portal|accessdate=17 March 2018|language=sh}}</ref> born 6 May 1994) is a Croatian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for English club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]]. Kova\u010di\u0107 is usually deployed as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]] or [[Midfielder#Deep-lying playmaker|deep-lying playmaker]], but he is considered to be a versatile midfielder, having played in different positions and adapted to playing either [[Midfielder#Winger|wide]] on the left or as an [[midfielder|attacking midfielder]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Who is Inter new boy Mateo Kovacic? |url=http://forzaitalianfootball.com/2013/02/who-is-inter-new-boy-mateo-kovacic/ |publisher=Forza Italian Football |date=3 February 2013 |accessdate=8 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nKova\u010di\u0107 began his professional career with [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] at the age of 16, with whom he won two consecutive league titles, before joining [[Inter Milan|Inter]] in 2013. After the [[2014\u201315 Inter Milan season|2014\u201315 season]], he moved to Real Madrid, where he won the Champions League on three occasions. He joined Chelsea on one-year loan in 2018, winning Europa League in the process. A full Croatian international since 2013, Kova\u010di\u0107 represented the nation at the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]], [[UEFA Euro 2016]] and the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], including a runner's up finish in the latter tournament. He is nicknamed ''Il Professore (The Professor).''<ref>{{cite news |title=Mateo Kovacic: Scout Report Inter's creative midfield talent |url=http://outsideoftheboot.com/2014/01/23/mateo-kovacic-scout-report/ |publisher=Outside of the Boot |date=23 January 2014 |accessdate=22 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Kovavic il migliore con la Croazia, soprannominato dai compagni \"il Professore\" |url=http://www.diggita.it/story.php?title=Kovavic_il_migliore_con_la_Croazia_soprannominato_dai_compagni_il_Professore-1 |publisher=diggita.it |date=26 March 2013 |accessdate=22 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923061008/http://www.diggita.it/story.php?title=Kovavic_il_migliore_con_la_Croazia_soprannominato_dai_compagni_il_Professore-1 |archive-date=23 September 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n===Youth career===\nBorn in [[Linz]], Austria, to [[Bosnian Croat]] parents who had moved there from [[Kotor Varo\u0161]] in Bosnia and Herzegovina, Kova\u010di\u0107 began playing at an early age at the local [[LASK Linz]]'s academy.<ref name=\"zidak\">{{cite news |url=http://www.jutarnji.hr/mateo-kovacic-kao-maradona--modric--pele---/905740/ |title=Meteor Kova\u010di\u0107: Svi su ludi za dje\u010dakom koji je ve\u0107 sa 13 igrao zrelo kao nekad Maradona |last=\u017didak |first=Tomislav |work=[[Jutarnji list]] |date=22 November 2010 |language=Croatian |accessdate=22 November 2010}}</ref> In 2007, when Kova\u010di\u0107 was 13, he was spotted by scouts from several prominent European clubs, including [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], [[Inter Milan]], [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] and [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], but his family opted to move to [[Zagreb]] instead, where he joined the [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb Academy|academy]] of Croatian giants [[NK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]].<ref name=\"zidak\"/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.jutarnji.hr/mateo-kovacic--kako-je-stvoren-igrac-od-100-milijuna-kuna/1082758/ |title=Cijela istina o Mateu Kova\u010di\u0107u |last=Cigoj |first=Mark |work=Jutarnji list |date=2 February 2013 |language=Croatian |accessdate=1 June 2014}}</ref>\nKova\u010di\u0107 suffered a serious injury in 2009 in which his leg was broken, but he returned to the pitch after a lengthy recovery on 31 May 2010, appearing in the last match of the [[Prva HNL Academy|Croatian under-17 academy league]], in a friendly 5\u20130 win against [[RNK Split]] under-17s.<ref name=\"kadeti\">{{cite news |url=http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/398143/nogomet-1-hnl/kadeti-dinama-za-naslov-prestigli-hajduk |title=Kadeti Dinama za naslov prestigli Hajduk |last=Rupnik |first=Borna |date=31 May 2010 |publisher=[[Sportnet.hr|Sportnet]] |language=Croatian |accessdate=22 November 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Dinamo Zagreb===\nKova\u010di\u0107 started training with the club's senior squad under manager, [[Vahid Halilhod\u017ei\u0107]], four months later, on 6 October 2010,<ref name=\"vahid\">{{cite news |url=http://sportske.jutarnji.hr/mateo-kovacic-od-danas-trenira-sa-seniorima-dinama--plasi-me-nadimak-hrvatski-messi/892846/ |title=Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107 od danas trenira sa seniorima Dinama: Pla\u0161i me nadimak Hrvatski Messi |date=6 October 2010 |newspaper=[[Sportske novosti]] |language=Croatian |accessdate=20 November 2010}}</ref> but continued to appear for the club in academy league matches during October. Later that month, it was reported by the local sports daily, ''[[Sportske novosti]]'', that [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]'s chief scout, Steve Rowley, had arrived in Zagreb to watch him perform in under-17 matches against [[HNK Cibalia|Cibalia]] and [[NK Zagreb]].<ref name=\"sportske\">{{cite news |url=http://sportske.jutarnji.hr/arsenal-dosao-po-matea-kovacica--dinamo-nasao-novo-cudo-od-djeteta---miralema-ramica/899213/ |title=Arsenal do\u0161ao po Matea Kova\u010di\u0107a, Dinamo na\u0161ao novo \u010dudo od djeteta&nbsp;\u2014 Miralema Rami\u0107a |date=29 October 2010 |newspaper=Sportske novosti |language=Croatian |accessdate=22 November 2010}}</ref>\n\nKova\u010di\u0107 eventually had his professional league debut in the [[2010\u201311 Croatian First Football League]] away match against [[NK Hrvatski dragovoljac|Hrvatski Dragovoljac]] on 20 November 2010, in which he scored Dinamo's fourth goal in their 6\u20130 win.<ref name=\"debut\">{{cite news |url=http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/407740/nogomet-1-hnl/i-kovacic-strijelac-u-dinamovoj-sestici |title=I Kova\u010di\u0107 strijelac u Dinamovoj \u0161estici |last=Rupnik |first=Borna |date=20 November 2010 |publisher=Sportnet |language=Croatian |accessdate=20 November 2010}}</ref> This made him the youngest goalscorer in the history of the league, at the age of 16 years and 198 days, breaking the record set only a week earlier by [[Dino \u0160pehar]] who had scored for [[NK Osijek]] at the age of 16 years and 278 days on 13 November 2010.<ref name=\"record\">{{cite news |url=http://www.tportal.hr/sport/TcomPrvaHNL/97374/Mateo-Kovacic-najmladi-je-strijelac-Prve-HNL.html |title=Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107 najmla\u0111i je strijelac Prve HNL |date=20 November 2010 |publisher=TPortal |language=Croatian |accessdate=20 November 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"spehar\">{{cite news |url=http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/407385/nogomet-1-hnl/spehar-spasio-bijelo-plave |title=\u0160pehar spasio bijelo-plave |last=Plav\u010di\u0107 |first=Mario |date=13 November 2010 |work=Sportnet.hr |language=Croatian |accessdate=22 November 2010}}</ref> In his first senior season with Dinamo Zagreb he managed to appear in 7 matches, making a contribution in winning the league title.\n\nIn the [[2011\u201312 Croatian First Football League|2011\u201312]] season, Kova\u010di\u0107 rapidly established himself as a first team regular. He played mainly in the position of left midfielder in 4\u20132\u20133\u20131 system. In the beginning of the season, he helped the team reach the Group Stage of the season's [[2011\u201312 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] for the first time in 12 years. Being only 17 years old, he appeared in the starting lineup of Dinamo's first group match against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]. He finished his first European season with Dinamo by scoring a goal against [[Olympique Lyonnais]] in the last game of the Group Stage in [[Zagreb]] and thus became the second youngest ever scorer in the Champions League. In the domestic league, he was a regular starter, appearing in 25 league matches and scoring five goals in the process. During a league match against [[NK Lu\u010dko]], he became the youngest player to wear the captain's armband in Dinamo's history, taking the captaincy from [[Leandro Cufre]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kva\u010di\u0107 najmla\u0111i kapetan u Dnamovoj povijesti |url=http://www.tportal.hr/sport/prvaliga/145385/Kovacic-najmladi-kapetan-Dinama-u-povijesti.html#.UQm78x32_Wo |date=27 August 2011 |work=Tportal.hr |accessdate=31 January 2013}}</ref> It was another successful season for him in domestic competitions as he appeared in 32 domestic league and cup matches during that season, helping Dinamo to win their seventh consecutive league title. He also scored in the [[Croatian Football Cup|Croatian Cup]] final against [[NK Osijek]] on [[Maksimir Stadium]]. In December 2011, he was named [[Croatian Footballer of the Year#Hope of the Year|Croatian Football Hope of the Year]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Kova\u010di\u0107u trofej Nada godine: Liga prvaka je bila u\u017eivancija |url=http://www.24sata.hr/nogomet/kovacicu-trofej-nada-godine-liga-prvaka-je-bila-uzivancija-248104 |newspaper=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata]] |date=31 December 2011 |language=Croatian |accessdate=31 December 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn the beginning of [[2012\u201313 Croatian First Football League|2012\u201313]] season, he suffered a metatarsal bone injury that caused him to miss several games on the club's qualifying road to another Champions League. He returned just in time to play in Dinamo's first Champions League game against [[FC Porto|Porto]]. Kova\u010di\u0107 played in all six Dinamo Zagreb's matches in the [[2012\u201313 UEFA Champions League group stage]], against Porto, [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] and [[FC Dynamo Kyiv|Dynamo Kyiv]]. He continued to impress with his mature performances at a young age during the first half of the season. In October 2012, he was nominated for [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]], an award given by sports journalists to a young player from Europe perceived to have been the most impressive during a season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kova\u010di\u0107 kandidat za presti\u017enu nagradu \"Golden Boy 2012.\" |url=http://www.24sata.hr/nogomet/kovacic-kandidat-za-prestiznu-nagradu-golden-boy-2012-287471 |newspaper=24sata |date=20 October 2012 |language=Croatian |accessdate=31 January 2013}}</ref> During the season's winter break, Dinamo's board threw away the speculations about Kova\u010di\u0107 leaving the club in the near future by saying they are building a new team around him and another rising star, [[Alen Halilovi\u0107]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kova\u010di\u0107a i Halilovi\u0107a ne\u0107emo prodati! |url=http://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/dinamo-sporting-nam-se-nije-javio-kovacica-i-halilovica-necemo-prodati/652404.aspx |publisher=index.hr |date=15 December 2012 |language=Croatian |accessdate=8 April 2013}}</ref> However, on 30 January 2013, the media surprisingly revealed Kova\u010di\u0107 was sold to Italian [[Serie A]] club Inter Milan.\n\nDuring his time with Dinamo, Kova\u010di\u0107 won two domestic league titles and two Croatian Cup titles, appearing in a total of 73 official matches, including 12 appearances in the UEFA Champions League.\n\n===Inter Milan===\n[[File:Mateo Kovacic.jpg|170px|right|thumb|Kova\u010di\u0107 with Inter in February 2013.]]\n\nOn 31 January 2013, Kova\u010di\u0107 agreed to a transfer to Inter Milan. It was revealed the deal was worth \u20ac15&nbsp;million in total, with \u20ac11&nbsp;million paid immediately and \u20ac4&nbsp;million when and if Inter qualifies for the [[UEFA Champions League]].<ref name=\"Maglia 10\">{{cite news |title=Inter, Kovacic da 10, Maglia e calcio senza paura |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/02-02-2013/inter-kovacic-10-video-maglia-calcio-senza-paura-914107775713.shtml |first=Luca |last=Taidelli |newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]] |date=2 February 2013 |language=Italian |accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref> Upon his arrival, Kova\u010di\u0107 was given the number 10 shirt, previously worn by [[Wesley Sneijder]].<ref name=\"Maglia 10\"/>\n\n====2012\u201313 season====\nKova\u010di\u0107 made his Inter Milan debut three days later on 3 February, coming on as a half-time substitute in a [[2012\u201313 Serie A|Serie A]] match against [[S.S. Robur Siena|Siena]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Siena-Inter 3\u20131, Stramaccioni affonda sotto i gol di Sestu e Emeghara |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Siena/03-02-2013/siena-inter-3-1-male-nerazzurri-sestu-emeghara-dominano--914124870634.shtml |first=Valerio |last=Clari |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=3 February 2013 |language=Italian |accessdate=8 April 2013}}</ref> On 14 February, Kova\u010di\u0107 made his European debut before the home crowd at [[San Siro]] in [[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] match against [[CFR Cluj]]. He provided the winning assist for [[Rodrigo Palacio]], who made it 2\u20130 for Inter, impressing the crowd with his performance, and was given standing ovations while being substituted off in the 89th minute.<ref>{{cite news |title=Inter-Cluj 2\u20130: Doppio Palacio, ottimo Kovacic, ma infortunio per Milito |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/14-02-2013/inter-cluj-2-0-doppio-palacio-ottimo-kovacic-ma-infortunio-milito-923391317.shtml |first=Valerio |last=Clari |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=15 February 2013 |language=Italian |accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref> He also played full 90 minutes in the 3\u20130 away win against CFR Cluj as Inter proceeded to the next round of the [[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Europa League, Cluj-Inter 0\u20133: doppietta di Guarin, poi Benassi. Paura Ranocchia |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/21-02-2013/cluj-inter-0-3-doppietta-guarin-poi-benassi-ma-paura-ranocchia-92118521931.shtml |first=Valerio |last=Clari |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=21 February 2013 |language=Italian |accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nKova\u010di\u0107 made his first domestic league start for Inter in the next round of Serie A in a 1\u20134 away loss against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]]. In the round of 16 of the UEFA Europa League, Inter was drawn to play against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]]. After a 3\u20130 loss in London, Inter needed a 4\u20130 win in [[Milan]] to proceed to the next round. The match ended in a 4\u20131 win for Inter after the match went into extra time, with Kova\u010di\u0107 playing as a starter. He impressed with his composure and playmaking ability, once again receiving ovations by the fans.<ref>{{cite news |title=Inter-Tottenham 4\u20131, Cassano da applausi, ma non-basta: Spurs ai quarti |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/14-03-2013/europa-league-inter-tottenham-92474067493.shtml |first=Valerio |last=Clari |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=14 March 2013 |language=Italian |accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref> Then-Inter manager [[Andrea Stramaccioni]] hailed his performances on several occasions, describing him as a \"star for the future\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Inter Milan coach Andrea Stramaccioni hails Mateo Kovacic |url=http://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/inter-milan/news/stramaccioni-hails-kovacic_74900.html |last=Mondal |first=Subhankar |date=18 March 2013 |publisher=Sportsmole.co.uk |accessdate=8 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, Kova\u010di\u0107 was a starter in his first ''[[Derby d'Italia]]'' against Juventus at San Siro. The derby ended in a 1\u20132 win for Juventus, with Kova\u010di\u0107 starting the action that resulted in Rodrigo Palacio's 1\u20131 equalizer.<ref>{{cite news |title=Inter-Juve. Con Kovacic e Pirlo, precisione al potere |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/SerieA/Bigmatch/31-03-2013/inter-juve-kovacic-pirlo-precisione-potere-92754618835.shtml |first=Andrea |last=Schianchi |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=31 March 2013 |language=Italian |accessdate=31 March 2013}}</ref> Kova\u010di\u0107 was a starter in Inter's next Serie A match, a 0\u20132 away win against [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]], as well as in their surprising 3\u20134 loss to [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]] at San Siro, where he provided an assist for [[Ricky \u00c1lvarez]]'s goal.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sampdoria-Inter 0\u20132, decide la doppietta di Palacio |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Sampdoria/03-04-2013/solito-palacio-stende-samp-inter-stramaccioni-respirano-92805504703.shtml |first=Jacopo |last=Gerna |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=4 April 2013 |language=Italian |accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Inter-Atalanta 3\u20134, tripletta di Denis fra errori, botte e rimonte |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/07-04-2013/inter-atalanta-3-4-tripletta-denis-errori-botte-rimonte-92875894700.shtml |first=Valerio |last=Clari |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=8 April 2013 |language=Italian |accessdate=29 August 2013}}</ref> By the end of the second half of the season, he was a starter in all of the club's Serie A fixtures, as Inter finished in disappointing ninth place on the Serie A table. In May, he was given the \"Gentleman Revelation of the Year\" award, awarded by Inter fans.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zanetti fa 13: vince ancora il Gentleman Kovacic e De Sciglio i migliori giovani |url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2013/maggio/09/Zanetti_vince_ancora_Gentleman_Kovacic_ga_0_20130509_a099669c-b86c-11e2-bc10-72b41185888f.shtml |first=Francesco |last=Velluzzi |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=9 May 2013 |language=Italian |accessdate=29 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n====2013\u201314 season====\nKova\u010di\u0107 missed most of the pre-season training with the squad due to series of small injuries,<ref>{{cite web |title=Kovacic out seven days, will miss first friendly match |url=http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/07/16/kovacic-out-seven-days-will-miss-first-friendly-match/ |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=16 July 2013 |publisher=fedenerazzurra.com |accessdate=31 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Kovacic to miss another 10 days, out against Hamburg and Chelsea |url=http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/07/27/cds-kovacic-to-miss-another-10-days-out-against-hamburg-and-chelsea/ |newspaper=Corriere dello Sport |date=27 July 2013 |publisher=fedenerazzurra.com |accessdate=31 January 2014}}</ref> and made his comeback just few days before the first official match of the new season, a Coppa Italia match against [[Cittadella]] at Stadio Giuseppe Meazza.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kovacic ready to return versus Cittadella |url=http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/08/13/kovacic-ready-to-return-versus-cittadella/ |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=13 August 2013 |publisher=fedenerazzurra.com}}</ref> During the pre-season interviews, new Inter manager [[Walter Mazzarri]] hinted Kova\u010di\u0107 would be given a new role on the pitch, a role similar to [[Marek Ham\u0161\u00edk]]'s in Napoli.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mazzarri: \"Non vendo fumo, Kovacic alla Hamsik\" |url=http://it.eurosport.yahoo.com/notizie/calcio-in-trentino-mazzarri-non-vendo-fumo-kovacic-110123735.html |publisher=Eurosport |date=11 July 2013 |language=Italian |accessdate=31 January 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224144135/http://it.eurosport.yahoo.com/notizie/calcio-in-trentino-mazzarri-non-vendo-fumo-kovacic-110123735.html |archivedate=24 February 2014  }}</ref> During the first half of the season, Kova\u010di\u0107 played regularly, although he struggled with adjusting to his new tactical role.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mazzola: \"Kovacic is still not ready\" |url=http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/10/31/mazzola-kovacic-is-still-not-ready/ |work=Novastadio |date=31 October 2013 |publisher=fedenerazzurra.com |accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref> Kova\u010di\u0107 made his first assist of the season in the match against [[A.S. Livorno Calcio|Livorno]], when he delivered an assist for [[Yuto Nagatomo]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Zanetti was the main event but everyone forgot about Kovacic |url=http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/11/10/zanetti-was-the-main-event-but-everyone-forgot-about-kovacic/ |work=Sky Italia |date=10 November 2013 |publisher=fedenerazzurra.com |accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref> Unlike the previous season under manager Andrea Stramaccioni, Kova\u010di\u0107 was not a regular starter during the 2013\u201314 season. In 32 Serie A matches played, he started only 14, playing the entire 90 minutes on just eight occasions.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ibrulj |first1=Sa\u0161a |title=Can Mateo Kovacic Become a Regular at Inter Milan This Season? |url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2136193-can-mateo-kovacic-become-a-regular-at-inter-milan-this-season |publisher=bleacherreport.com |accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref> He received the chance to restore his confidence towards the end of the season, as he was Mazzarri's first-choice in the midfield in Inter's last six matches. On 10 May, in [[Javier Zanetti]]'s last competitive match at the San Siro, Kova\u010di\u0107 made three assists in 4\u20131 victory over [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Inter 4\u20131 Lazio |url=http://www.inter.it/en/match_center/4041 |publisher=inter.it |accessdate=13 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n====2014\u201315 season====\nAfter being subjected to persistent transfer speculation over the summer, in September 2014, Kova\u010di\u0107 was offered a contract extension until 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kemp |first1=Jamie |title=Barcelona bid for Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107 rejected by Inter Milan |url=http://www.insidespanishfootball.com/123331/barcelona-bid-for-mateo-kovacic-rejected-by-inter-milan/ |website=insidespanishfootball |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915184540/http://www.insidespanishfootball.com/123331/barcelona-bid-for-mateo-kovacic-rejected-by-inter-milan/ |archivedate=15 September 2014  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Barcelona Transfer News: Dani Alves to Leave in 2015, Mateo Kovacic Bid Revealed |url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2184122-barcelona-transfer-news-dani-alves-to-leave-in-2015-mateo-kovacic-bid-revealed |publisher=bleacherreport.com |accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Inter to lock down Kovacic and Icardi until 2019 |url=http://forzaitalianfootball.com/2014/09/inter-to-lock-down-kovacic-and-icardi-until-2019/ |accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref> He started the season in strong fashion, scoring a [[hat-trick]] in the second leg of Europa League [[2014\u201315 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round#Play-off round|play-off round]] against [[Stjarnan]] on 28 August.<ref>{{cite news |title=Inter, tutto facile: Stjarnan battuto 6\u20130 |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Inter/28-08-2014/inter-tutto-facile-stjarnan-battuto-6-0-90282903797.shtml |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=Italian |date=28 August 2014 |accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Mazzarri promuove Kovacic 'Cresce nel modo giusto' |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Inter/28-08-2014/inter-mazzarri-kovacic-sta-crescendmodo-giusto-90285455372.shtml |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140915074213/http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Inter/28-08-2014/inter-mazzarri-kovacic-sta-crescendmodo-giusto-90285455372.shtml |url-status=dead |archive-date=15 September 2014 |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=Italian |date=28 August 2014 |accessdate=29 August 2014 }}</ref> He scored his first league goal for Inter and assisted twice in a 7\u20130 win over [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] on 14 September 2014.<ref>{{cite news |title=Inter Milan7-0 Sassuolo |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29198823 |accessdate=14 September 2014 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=14 September 2014}}</ref> He scored the club's only goal in a 1\u20131 away draw with [[U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo|Palermo]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Mateo Kovacic scored his second goal in as many matches as Inter Milan fought back from a goal down to draw with Palermo. |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29277861 |date=21 September 2014 |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=28 September 2014}}</ref> He also scored the opening goal in a 2\u20130 win against [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]] and scored a wonder goal in a 2\u20132 drawn against Lazio. On 6 January 2015, he was sent-off in a 1\u20131 draw with Juventus for a foul on [[Stephan Lichtsteiner]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Juventus 1\u20131 Inter Milan |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30687617 |accessdate=7 January 2015 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=6 January 2014}}</ref> Three days later, Kova\u010di\u0107 renewed his contract with Inter until June 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kova\u010di\u0107 extends Inter deal till 2019 |url=http://www.inter.it/en/news/47286 |accessdate=9 January 2015 |work=[[Inter Milan|inter.it]] |date=9 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Real Madrid===\n[[File:Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107 2015.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Kova\u010di\u0107 playing for Real Madrid in a Champions League match against Shakhtar Donetsk in 2015.]]\n\nOn 16 August 2015, Inter manager [[Roberto Mancini]] confirmed the club was forced to sell Kova\u010di\u0107 to Real Madrid due to [[UEFA Financial Fair Play Regulations|Financial Fair Play]] regulations. Speaking during a press conference after a friendly against Greek club [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]], Mancini said, \"There are rules that have to be respected. I don't think anyone wanted this to happen but we have the Financial Fair Play regulations to follow. We're all sorry about it: myself, the president, the management and the players themselves.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.inter.it/en/news/48790 |title=Mancini: \"We had our chances\" |date=16 August 2015 |publisher=[[Inter Milan]] |accessdate=18 August 2015}}</ref> Real Madrid also confirmed the transfer two days later, announcing Kova\u010di\u0107 had signed a six-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2015/08/official-announcement-mateo-kova%C4%8Di%C4%87 |title=Official announcement: Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107 |date=18 August 2015 |publisher=Real Madrid CF |accessdate=18 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/aug/16/real-madrid-internazionale-mateo-kovacic |title=Real Madrid agree \u20ac32m fee with Internazionale to sign Mateo Kovacic |last1=Christenson |first1=Marcus |last2=Romano |first2=Fabrizio |date=16 August 2015 |accessdate=28 August 2015 |work=The Guardian}}</ref> The transfer fee was \u20ac29&nbsp;million, according to Inter's financial filing in the section Management Report ({{lang-it|Relazione sulla Gestione}}).<ref>F.C. Internazionale Milano S.p.A. ''bilancio'' (financial report and accounts) on 30 June 2015 PDF purchased from [[Camera di Commercio, Industria, Agricoltura e Artigianato|CCIAA]] (in Italian)</ref> On 19 August, Kova\u010di\u0107 was unveiled as a new player by Real Madrid at the [[Santiago Bernab\u00e9u Stadium]], where it was revealed he would wear the number 16 shirt for the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2015/08/kovacic-being-at-the-biggest-club-in-the-world-is-really-special |title=Kovacic: \"Being at the biggest club in the world is really special\" |date=19 August 2015 |publisher=Real Madrid CF |accessdate=19 August 2015}}</ref> Kova\u010di\u0107 became the fifth Croatian player, after [[Robert Prosine\u010dki]], [[Davor \u0160uker]], [[Robert Jarni]] and [[Luka Modri\u0107]], to join Real Madrid.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kova\u010di\u0107 peti Hrvat u dresu Kraljevskog kluba |url=http://sport.hrt.hr/295444/kovacic-peti-hrvat-u-dresu-kraljevskog-kluba |website=HRT Sport |publisher=Hrt |accessdate=3 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Cristiano Ronaldo entrenando.jpg|thumb|left|Kova\u010di\u0107 (left) warming up with [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] and [[Casemiro]] during the 2015\u201316 season]]\n\nFour days after his presentation, he made his debut as a 70th-minute substitute for [[Isco]] as Real Madrid began the [[La Liga|Liga]] [[2015\u201316 La Liga|season]] with a goalless draw at promoted [[Sporting de Gij\u00f3n]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Sporting spoil Ben\u00edtez debut |url=http://www.marca.com/en/2015/08/23/en/football/real_madrid/1440360649.html |accessdate=23 August 2015 |work=Marca|location=Spain |date=23 August 2015}}</ref> He scored his first goal in an 8\u20130 home win over [[Malm\u00f6 FF]] on 8 December 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000634/match=2015746/postmatch/report/index.html |title=Ronaldo rampant as Madrid put eight past Malm\u00f6 |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=8 December 2015}}</ref> On 3 January 2016, Kova\u010di\u0107 received a straight red card in a 2\u20132 draw at [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] for a foul on [[Jo\u00e3o Cancelo]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Begley |first1=Emlyn |title=Valencia 2\u20132 Real Madrid |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/35155362 |accessdate=3 January 2016 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=3 January 2016}}</ref> Until the end of his first season with ''Los Blancos'', he made a total of 34 appearances. In the opening months of the season, he was used quite regularly by then Real Madrid manager [[Rafael Ben\u00edtez]], playing in almost every midfield position there is&nbsp;\u2013 sometimes central, sometimes wide, sometimes further forward. However, after [[Zinedine Zidane]] replaced Ben\u00edtez in early January, Kova\u010di\u0107's appearances became increasingly infrequent. With the Frenchman preferring to use a very defined starting 11 whenever possible instead of the more specific-lineups-for-specific-opponents approach employed by his predecessor, there was little room for Kova\u010di\u0107. He made eight appearances and scored one goal en Real Madrid's route to the [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League]] title.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000638/match=2015789/postmatch/report/index.html |title=Spot-on Real Madrid defeat Atl\u00e9tico in final again |date=28 May 2016 |publisher=UEFA}}</ref>\n\nKova\u010di\u0107 scored his first Liga goal on 29 January 2017 in a 3\u20130 win over [[Real Sociedad]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38719239|title=Real Madrid 3\u20130 Real Sociedad|date=29 January 2017|publisher=bbc.co.uk}}</ref> He was a part-time starter when Madrid won the [[2016\u201317 La Liga]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laliga.es/noticias/real-madrid-campeon-de-laliga-santander-2016-17|title=El Real Madrid, campe\u00f3n de LaLiga Santander 2016/17|date=21 May 2017|work=laliga.es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39926301|title=Real Madrid win La Liga title with victory at Malaga|date=21 May 2017|work=bbc.com}}</ref> and the [[2016\u201317 UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2017/matches/round=2000787/match=2019641/postmatch/report/index.html|title=Majestic Real Madrid win Champions League in Cardiff|date=3 June 2017|work=uefa.com}}</ref>\n\nDuring the [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League]], Kova\u010di\u0107 made six appearances when Madrid won their third consecutive\u2014and 13th overall\u2014UEFA Champions League title.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2018/matches/round=2000885/match=2021711/postmatch/report/index.html|title=Madrid beat Liverpool to complete hat-trick|date=26 May 2018|work=uefa.com}}</ref>\n\n===Chelsea===\nOn 8 August 2018, Kova\u010di\u0107 joined [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] on a one-year loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/08/official-announcement-mateo-kovacic|title=Official announcement: Mateo Kovacic|date=8 August 2018|work=realmadrid.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2018/8/8/courtois-and-kovacic-deals-agreed|title=Courtois and Kovacic deals agreed|date=8 August 2018|work=chelseafc.com}}</ref> He made his debut in a 3\u20132 home win against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on 18 August, appearing as a second-half substitute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.givemesport.com/1374987-mateo-kovacics-individual-highlights-against-arsenal-have-now-emerged|title=Mateo Kovacic's individual highlights against Arsenal have now emerged|date=19 August 2018|work=GiveMeSport}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 July 2019, Kova\u010di\u0107 completed a permanent transfer to Chelsea, signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2019/07/official-announcement-kovacic|title=Official Announcement: Kovacic|date=1 July 2019|work=realmadrid.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2019/07/01/mateo-kovacic-joins-chelsea-on-a-permanent-deal|title=Mateo Kovacic joins Chelsea on a permanent deal|date=1 July 2019|work=chelseafc.com}}</ref> Kova\u010di\u0107 scored his first goal for Chelsea on 27 November 2019, in a 2\u20132 [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] draw against Valencia at the [[Mestalla Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chowdhury |first1=Saj |title=Valencia 2\u20132 Chelsea |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50519896 |accessdate=28 November 2019 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 November 2019}}</ref> On 7 December 2019, he scored his first [[Premier League]] goal in a 1\u20133 away loss to [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=McNulty |first1=Phil |title=Everton 3\u20131 Chelsea |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50611310 |accessdate=7 December 2019 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=7 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n[[File:Mateo Kovacic - Croatia vs. Portugal, 10th June 2013.jpg|290px|thumb|Kova\u010di\u0107 with the national team in June 2013.]]\n\nKova\u010di\u0107 appeared for the Croatian national team at various youth levels, debuting in May 2008 in an under-14 friendly match against Slovakia.<ref name=\"hns\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hns-cff.hr/?ln=hr&w=statistike&repka=U&id=156397 |title=Statistike&nbsp;\u2014 Nastupi: Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107 |publisher=[[Croatian Football Federation]] |language=Croatian |accessdate=20 November 2010}}</ref> Since 2011, he was a regular member of the Croatia under-19 and under-21 teams. In August 2012, Kova\u010di\u0107 received his first competitive call-up for the [[Croatia national football team|Croatian senior team]] match against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]], but did not play because of injury.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0160timac pozvao Kova\u010di\u0107a |url=http://sportske.jutarnji.hr/igor-stimac-za-svicarsku-pozvao-malocu--vukusica--kovacica--sammir-jos-uvijek-na-cekanju/1044377/ |date=30 July 2012 |language=Croatian |accessdate=31 January 2013}}</ref> Subsequently, he received a call up for [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches in March 2013. He made his senior debut in a qualification match against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] on 22 March 2013, playing as a central midfielder alongside Luka Modri\u0107, instead of a regular team starter, [[Ognjen Vukojevi\u0107]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0160timac: \"Odluku o Kova\u010di\u0107u 'prelomio' sam sino\u0107, odigrao je za desetku\" |url=http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/458465/nogomet-reprezentacija/stimac-odluku-o-kovacicu-prelomio-sam-sinoc-odigrao-je-za-desetku/ |publisher=Sportnet |date=22 March 2013 |language=Croatian |accessdate=23 March 2013}}</ref> Four days later, he played against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] at [[Liberty Stadium]], coming on as a second-half substitute in a 1\u20132 win. His third match of the campaign came in June, when Croatia faced [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] in Zagreb and suffered a frustrating defeat as they were unable to score despite a string of good chances. By the end of the qualifiers, Kova\u010di\u0107 made two more competitive appearances for Croatia, as Croatia scraped into the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification&nbsp;\u2013 UEFA Second Round|FIFA World Cup play-offs]] having taken only one point from their last four qualifiers. Although he didn't participate in the scoreless first leg of the play-off against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] in [[Reykjav\u00edk]], Kova\u010di\u0107 started the second and decisive leg between the two national teams in Zagreb, making an assist for the team's second goal as they reached the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] finals 2\u20130 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ten-man Croatia reached the 2014 World Cup finals |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/24907602 |date=19 November 2013 |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=31 January 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 June 2014, Kova\u010di\u0107 was confirmed as a member of Croatia's [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] squad.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/croatia/10810185/Croatia-World-Cup-2014-squad.html |title=Croatia World Cup 2014 squad |date=2 June 2014 |work=The Telegraph |accessdate=19 June 2014}}</ref> He was in Croatia's starting team for the opening game of the tournament, a 3\u20131 defeat to World Cup hosts [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] at the [[Arena Corinthians]], S\u00e3o Paulo, where he played for his team for 60 minutes before being substituted.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/25285029 |title=Brazil 3\u20131 Croatia |date=12 June 2014 |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=20 June 2014}}</ref> He went to play all the remaining games in the group stage, as Croatia was eliminated in a group stage. On 7 June 2015, he scored his first international goal in a 4\u20130 victory over [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]], coming in his 20th appearance for the team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.croatiaweek.com/croatia-4-0-gibraltar-mission-accomplished-kovac|title=Croatia 4\u20130 Gibraltar: 'Mission Accomplished'- Kova\u010d|publisher=Croatia Week|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 June 2018, Kova\u010di\u0107 was selected in Croatia's 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportsnet.ca/soccer/modric-rakitic-headline-croatias-world-cup-squad|title=Modric, Rakitic headline Croatia's World Cup squad|publisher=Sportsnet|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref> On 22 June, Kova\u010di\u0107 provided an assist to his teammate [[Ivan Rakiti\u0107]] as he scored Croatia's third goal in a 3\u20130 win over [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in their second group stage match of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1249922/Live/International-FIFA-World-Cup-2018-Argentina-Croatia|title=Argentina 0\u20133 Croatia \u2013 FIFA World Cup 2018 Live|publisher=Whoscored.com|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref> Croatia was beaten 4\u20132 by [[France national football team|France]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup Final|the final]] on 15 July.<ref name=\"McNulty\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44754965|title=France 4\u20132 Croatia: France beat Croatia in thrilling World Cup final |publisher=BBC Sport |date=15 July 2018|access-date=15 July 2018|last=McNulty|first=Phil}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\n[[File:Mateo Kovacic 21032013 2 Zagrebello roberta f.jpg|170px|left|thumb|Kova\u010di\u0107 training with the [[Croatia national football team]] in March 2013]]\n\nKova\u010di\u0107 has been described as a great technician with excellent [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] abilities.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kovacic compared with Roberto Baggio |url=http://www.football-italia.net/30222/kovacic-compared-baggio |date=1 February 2013 |publisher=football-italia.net |accessdate=17 February 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Mehrotra\">{{cite web |last=Mehrotra |first=Aakriti |title=Mateo Kovacic: Scout Report&nbsp;\u2014 Inter's creative midfield talent |url=http://outsideoftheboot.com/2014/01/23/mateo-kovacic-scout-report/# |work=Outside of the Boot |accessdate=1 February 2014|date=22 January 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Stats Show Mateo Kovacic As One Of Europe's Best Dribblers |url=http://www.zimbio.com/Mateo+Kovacic/articles/Eyd0yinCbnH/Stats+Show+Mateo+Kovacic+One+Europe+Best+Dribblers |publisher=interfanclub.com |accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref> He is considered to be a versatile midfielder, having played in different midfield positions. He started off as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] at Dinamo Zagreb, but he transformed his game at Inter where he was deployed out wide and also as a central midfielder, functioning as a deep-lying playmaker, while being coached by Andrea Stramaccioni.<ref name=\"Mehrotra\"/> One of his trademarks is dropping deep to receive the ball and then driving forward, often performing his slalom runs.<ref name=\"Mehrotra\"/> Under the coach, Walter Mazzarri, he was often used in a more advanced position. Former manager [[Giovanni Trapattoni]] once claimed that Kova\u010di\u0107 knows how to really reach the ball from deep and drive up the pitch like a 'raging bull'.<ref name=MM>{{cite web |last=Higgins |first=Timm |title=Could Mateo Kovacic Be The Heir To Luka Modric's Crown? |url=http://www.managingmadrid.com/2017/2/10/14557684/could-mateo-kovacic-be-the-heir-to-luka-modrics-crown |work=Managing Madrid |accessdate=12 February 2017 |date=10 February 2017}}</ref> Proven by his pass completion percentages, Kova\u010di\u0107 is known for distributing the ball up the pitch.<ref name=MM />\n\n===Reception===\nThe Croatia under-17 manager, [[Martin Novoselac]], reportedly said of Kova\u010di\u0107, \"I haven't seen a youngster with so much talent since the days of Robert Prosine\u010dki,\" referring to his fast development and talent.<ref name=\"zidak\"/><ref name=\"vahid\"/> Kova\u010di\u0107 revealed that precisely Prosine\u010dki is the player he admired the most while growing up.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kova\u010di\u0107 otkrio Talijanima koga je 'snimao' |url=http://www.tportal.hr/sport/nogomet/242330/Kovacic-otkrio-Talijanima-koga-je-volio-gledati.html |publisher=Tportal.hr |date=8 February 2013 |language=Croatian |accessdate=12 May 2013}}</ref> His compatriot, [[Zvonimir Boban]], who played for [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] for over a decade, in an interview with [[Sky Italia]] in 2013 said, \"He has talents that could make him even better than me, he is an incredibly serious professional for someone his age. Kova\u010di\u0107 is a complete player. He is not a born regista but he is playing there now. He is a complete talent that can still grow&nbsp;\u2014 he has incredible potential.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Inter snap up Kovacic and Kuzmanovic |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/news/story/_/id/1320857/inter-snap-kovacic-kuzmanovic?cc=5739 |date=31 January 2013 |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=3 February 2013}}</ref> Trapattoni described him as \"a mixture of [[Kak\u00e1]] and [[Clarence Seedorf]]\", because of his style of play and technical characteristics.<ref>{{cite news |title='Kovacic is a mix of Kaka and Seedorf' \u2013 Trapattoni |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/10/italy/2013/11/24/4428536/kovacic-is-a-mix-of-kaka-and-seedorf-trapattoni |date=24 November 2013 |publisher=Goal.com |accessdate=5 December 2013}}</ref> Long-time Inter captain Javier Zanetti stated that, with the exception of [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]], who had arrived to Inter when he was 21, Kova\u010di\u0107 was the most promising youngster he had seen in his 19 years at the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=Face to face: Javier Zanetti |url=http://www.worldsoccer.com/features/face-to-face-javier-zanetti |first=Jamie |last=Rainbow |date=12 August 2013 |publisher=WorldSoccer |accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nKova\u010di\u0107 is a devout [[Catholicism|Roman Catholic]] and he attends church every Sunday.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107: Hrvati, uzdajmo se u Boga! Di\u010dimo se svojim i ne vrije\u0111ajmo druge |url=http://www.zupa-svanastazija.com/novost/mateo-kovacic-hrvati-uzdajmo-se-u-boga-dicimo-se-svojim-i-ne-vrijedajmo-druge/582/ |accessdate=22 June 2016}}</ref> He speaks five languages; English, Croatian, German, Spanish and Italian.<ref>{{cite news |title=El v\u00eddeo que demuestra que Kovacic habla \u00a15 idiomas! |date=7 December 2016 |publisher=Marca |url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/real-madrid/2016/12/07/58474b82e5fdeaba688b464e.html}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, he married his longtime girlfriend Izabel Andrijani\u0107.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107 o\u017eenio djevojku Izabel, na svadbi i zvijezde Reala |date=17 June 2017 |publisher=Ve\u010dernji list |url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/mateo-kovacic-ozenio-djevojku-izabel-na-svadbi-i-zvijezde-reala-1177259}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 3 March 2020}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Mateo Kovacic |url=http://www.whoscored.com/Players/93894/Show/Mateo-Kovacic |website=WhoScored.com |accessdate=3 November 2015}}</ref><ref name=Soccerway>{{Soccerway|mateo-kovai/156567}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup{{efn|Includes [[Croatian Football Cup]], [[Coppa Italia]], [[Copa del Rey]], [[FA Cup]]}}\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup{{efn|Includes [[EFL Cup]]}}\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other{{efn|Includes [[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]], [[UEFA Super Cup]], [[FIFA Club World Cup]]}}\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hrsport.net/nogomet/klubovi/dinamo/?igracID=16228&sID=22 |title=Mateo Kova\u010di\u0107&nbsp;\u2014 stats |publisher=hrsport.net |language=Croatian |accessdate=1 February 2013}}</ref>\n|[[2010\u201311 GNK Dinamo Zagreb season|2010\u201311]]\n|[[Croatian First Football League|Prva HNL]]\n|7||1||2||0||colspan=2|\u2014||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||9||1\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 GNK Dinamo Zagreb season|2011\u201312]]\n|Prva HNL\n|25||4||7||1||colspan=2|\u2014||12<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UCL\">Appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]]</ref>||1||colspan=2|\u2014||44||6\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 GNK Dinamo