91|relyear=1990|}}\n{{certification Table Entry|type=album|region=United States|artist=Various|title=Pretty woman|award=Platinum|number=3|certyear=1991|relyear=1990|}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==Musical adaptation==\n{{Main|Pretty Woman: The Musical}}\nA stage musical adaptation of the film opened on [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] on July 20, 2018 in previews, officially on August 16 at the [[Nederlander Theatre]].<ref name=olivia>Clement, Olivia. [http://www.playbill.com/article/pretty-woman-musical-finds-its-broadway-home-sets-summer-2018-opening# \" 'Pretty Woman' Musical Finds Its Broadway Home, Sets Summer 2018 Opening\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171124074450/http://www.playbill.com/article/pretty-woman-musical-finds-its-broadway-home-sets-summer-2018-opening |date=November 24, 2017 }} Playbill, November 22, 2017</ref> This follows an out-of-town tryout at the [[Oriental Theatre (Chicago)|Oriental Theatre]] in Chicago, which will run from March 13 to April 15, 2018. The musical has music and lyrics by [[Bryan Adams]] and [[Jim Vallance]]; the late [[Garry Marshall]] and [[J.F. Lawton]] wrote the book; and [[Jerry Mitchell]] is the director and choreographer.<ref name=play1>McPhee, Ryan. [http://www.playbill.com/article/jason-danieley-joins-broadway-bound-pretty-woman-musical# \"Jason Danieley Joins Broadway-Bound 'Pretty Woman' Musical\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007220556/http://www.playbill.com/article/jason-danieley-joins-broadway-bound-pretty-woman-musical |date=October 7, 2017 }} Playbill, October 6, 2017</ref> The Chicago and Broadway casts featured [[Samantha Barks]], in her Broadway debut as Vivian and [[Steve Kazee]] as Edward. Barks finished her run as Vivian on 21 July 2019 and was replaced by Jillian Mueller the following evening, with Brennin Hunt, of \u2018Rent\u2019 fame, assuming the role of Edward.<ref name=play1/> [[Orfeh]] portrayed Kit, and [[Jason Danieley]]  played Philip Stuckey. [[Eric Anderson (actor)|Eric Anderson]] portrayed the role of Mr. Thompson and Kingsley Leggs played the role of James Morse.<ref name=olivia/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n* {{IMDb title|0100405|Pretty Woman}}\n* {{AllRovi movie|39093|Pretty Woman}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|pretty_woman|Pretty Woman}}\n* {{Mojo title|prettywoman|Pretty Woman}}\n\n{{Garry Marshall}}\n{{Roy Orbison}}\n\n[[Category:1990 films]]\n[[Category:1990s romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:1990s sex comedy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:American sex comedy films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films about businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Films about prostitution in the United States]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Garry Marshall]]\n[[Category:Films featuring a Best Musical or Comedy Actress Golden Globe winning performance]]\n[[Category:Films scored by James Newton Howard]]\n[[Category:Films set in Beverly Hills, California]]\n[[Category:Films set in hotels]]\n[[Category:Films set in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Touchstone Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Roy Orbison]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pretty_Woman"}
